Description: African Red Slip Ware sherd of large pottery plate; brick red clay; stamped decoration; on the inside is a tondo with central leaf pattern; impressions that look like shoe imprints (?).
Production place: Made in: Tunis, El Mahrine workshop? (area)
Curator's comments: African Red Slip ware sherd from a plate. Hayes ARS stamp 'planta pedis' style A 148r and palm style 4 on ARS form 67. Published (Hayes 1972, 116, 252) dated 360-470. Late Roman Pottery. London.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (IF.088) (Phase 3)
